# Documentation Standards

## When to Update Docs
- New or changed HTTP endpoint (routes, handlers, DTOs, status codes)
- OIDC root routes (`/authorize`, `/token`, etc.) or `/api/v1` routes
- OIDC/federation/MFA/WebAuthn/SSO session behavior changes
- CSRF skip list changes in `internal/middlewares/csrf.go`
- New env vars in `internal/config/`
- Database schema changes (`cmd/migrations/sql/`)
- Platform admin or tenant membership authorization changes

## What to Document

### OpenAPI (required for `/api/v1` HTTP changes)
- swag annotations on handlers + `cmd/server/main.go` metadata (`@BasePath /api/v1`)
- Regenerate: `make swagger-load`
- Commit `docs/swagger.yaml`, `docs/swagger.json`, `docs/docs.go` together
- Root OIDC routes are **outside** swag — update feature + testing docs instead

### Feature docs (when behavior changes)

Use the standard sections in [docs/features/](features/): summary, endpoints, flow, persistence, code map, config, frontend, testing link.

| Feature doc | Testing doc | Update when |
|-------------|-------------|-------------|
| `docs/features/OIDC.md` | `docs/testing/OIDC_CURL.md` | `/authorize`, `/token`, `/userinfo`, JWKS, PKCE |
| `docs/features/SSO_SESSION.md` | `docs/testing/SSO_CURL.md` | `iam_session`, SSO, logout |
| `docs/features/FEDERATION.md` | `docs/testing/FEDERATION_CURL.md` | Google federation, tenant IdP admin |
| `docs/features/PASSKEY_MFA.md` | `docs/testing/PASSKEY_MFA_CURL.md` | WebAuthn, MFA TOTP/recovery |
| `docs/features/MULTI_TENANT.md` | — | memberships, tenant select/switch |
| `docs/features/AUTHORIZATION.md` | — | platform admin, tenant roles |

Also update [docs/README.md](README.md) hub if DB tables or Redis keys change.

### Human docs
- `README.md` — setup, `make` targets, link to `docs/README.md`
- [`CONTRIBUTING.md`](../../../CONTRIBUTING.md) (repo root) — contribution expectations
- `cmd/server/.env.example` — new required env vars (no secrets)

## Style
- Concise and practical — include real `make` / `curl` examples with correct path prefix
- Verify paths and commands exist in this repo
- Outdated docs are worse than no docs
